%% TrustyAI Service Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant TAS as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Storage as PVC / Database<br/>JDBC

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Model Monitoring (ModelMesh)
    participant MM as ModelMesh Serving
    MM->>TAS: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS (internal certs)
    TAS->>Storage: Store inference data<br/>Filesystem / JDBC
    participant Prom as Prometheus
    Prom->>TAS: GET /q/metrics<br/>80/TCP HTTP plaintext

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 2: TrustyAI Service Model Monitoring (KServe)
    participant KServe as KServe InferenceService
    KServe->>TAS: InferenceLogger callback<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (Raw) / 80/TCP HTTP (Serverless)
    TAS->>Storage: Store inference data<br/>Filesystem / JDBC

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 3: LM Evaluation Job Execution
    participant LMESCtrl as LMES Controller
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant EvalPod as Evaluation Pod
    participant ModelEP as Model Endpoint<br/>(HF/OpenAI/vLLM)

    LMESCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create eval pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    LMESCtrl->>EvalPod: exec (WebSocket)<br/>Manage evaluation lifecycle
    EvalPod->>ModelEP: Inference requests<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, API key auth

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 4: Guardrails Orchestrator Request Flow
    participant GORCH as Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8032/TCP HTTPS
    participant GenIS as Generation<br/>InferenceService
    participant DetIS as Detector<br/>InferenceServices
    participant BuiltIn as Built-in Detector<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant GW as Gateway Sidecar<br/>8090/TCP HTTP

    Client->>Route: HTTPS request<br/>443/TCP TLS (reencrypt)
    Route->>GORCH: Forward request<br/>8032/TCP HTTPS
    GORCH->>GenIS: Generation request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS Optional TLS
    GORCH->>DetIS: Detection request<br/>HTTP/HTTPS Optional TLS
    GORCH->>BuiltIn: Regex detection<br/>8080/TCP HTTP localhost
    GW->>GORCH: Streaming guardrails<br/>8032/TCP HTTPS TLS
    GORCH-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>Client: HTTPS Response
